        <subsection xml:id="">
          <title>Capacitors</title>
          <p>A capacitor is an electrical component that stores and releases electrical energy in an electric field. It consists of two conductive plates separated by an insulating material called a <term>dielectric</term>. When a voltage is applied across the plates, electric charges accumulate on the plates, creating an electric field between them.</p>
          <p>When a capacitor is charged in this way, energy is stored in the electric field.  Capacitors can be discharged to quickly provide short bursts of power.  They are often used for energy storage, filtering, and smoothing voltage fluctuations.</p>
