        <subsection xml:id="">
          <title>Inductors</title>
          <p>An inductor is an electrical component that stores energy in a magnetic field when current flows through it. It consists of a coil of wire wound around a core material. When current passes through the coil, a magnetic field is created around it, and this field stores energy. Any device which uses electrical current to produce a magnetic field is an inductor.</p>
          <p>An inductor is like a "magnetic energy storage" device. It resists changes in current and helps regulate and control the flow of electricity. They are used in applications like filtering, energy storage, and electromagnets. </p>
          <figure xml:id="fig_inductors">
            <caption>Magnetic Field surrounding inductor, toroidal inductors </caption>
