        <subsection xml:id="">
          <title>Diodes</title>
          <p>A <term>diode</term> is an electrical component that allows current to flow in one direction while blocking it in the opposite direction. It acts as a <q>one-way valve</q> for electric current. Diodes are made from semiconductor materials and have two terminals: an anode (positive side) and a cathode (negative side).</p>
          <p><term>Rectifier Diodes</term> are used for converting AC to direct current DC (rectification). </p>
          <p><term>Zener diodes</term> are used for voltage regulation and voltage reference applications. They maintain a nearly constant voltage across their terminals regardless of current changes.</p>
          <p><term>Light Emitting Diodes</term> (LEDs)  emit light when current flows through them. They are used for indicators, displays, lighting, and optical communication.</p>
